Jul 26 2009 	enjoyable but not outstanding	We had picked this property for a post-honeymoon weekend get-away particularly because of supposedly good reputation and also the location. Having stayed at many beach properties it was time for a change. The location is rather unexciting; if you expect real, high dunes around it or in front of your window, you will be disappointed. The desert around it is fairly flat. The poolside layout and the multiple pools are very nice and enjoyable; so is the bar that you can actually swim to. The Italian Restaurant was closed, which was not highlighted to us upon making the reservation and this left us with very little choice on the F&amp;B side. either the international restaurant (buffet) which also has a 2-pages Indian a la carte menu, or the highly overpriced Arabic dinner &amp; show (where none of the employees seem to know the exact opening timings for). The rooms are pleasant but considering the space should not be a constraint if you build a hotel out in the desert with nothing around you, they are very small. the terraces are pleasant but do not feature any fans - which again, having the desert location, might be something useful.The bar - wide, open and lovely decorated - has the exact number of 3 fans ....unluckily we were the 4th couple to arrive and therefore no fan was available. Kind of unlogic, when you think of layout and purpose of the hotel, that they would only provide 3 fans throughout a big wide rooftop bar. The food was a big disappointement throughout the stay. The same menu seems to apply for all outlets, and the word deep-fried applies to every item on the bar menu. So generally speaking, we still had a good time because we enjoyed a weekend away, but the product is not have as thrilling as they publish it in the massively thick photo-book that is displayed at the Front Office.The only thing that really bothered us, was the lack of service. This is by far not a 5-star-service quality and by the end we were just taking it easy and actually starting to joke about it, finding it rather amusing, to see a consistency in non-existent customer care. (greeting, smiling, opening doors, volunteering to assist etc.) The staff seems just utterly un-caring, not interested and could not be bothered with the guest. Friendly smiles are rare, pro-active guest approach does not exist. Our expecatiatons in that regard were certainly high, and as you are paying premium rates, you would expect at least a bare minimum of customer service. There are about 2 or 3 motivated souls in the F&amp;B department who do make an effort to enquire, to talk to the guest and to ensure you are pleased with whatever you want. All others seem to be not happy and motivated. What a pity though, because that is what makes a difference whether or not a guest returns. For a 2day weekend it was fine; not thrilling and not necessarily to be recommended if you have high expectations on guest service. One of the reasons it was nice, was because the hotel seemed quite empty. Would not suggest to go over a holiday period, because than it might be rather crowded at the pool. The walls of the guestrooms are very thin and you virtually hear your neighbours and the room above you too. The Spa is nice, treatments are very good, but again the extra step of customer service is not done.All in one, ok but not outstanding.	
Jun 8 2009 	Tranquil relaxing hideaway in the middle of the desert	We were looking for a long weekend away from the hustle and bustle of Abu Dhabi and we found exactly what we were looking for at Bab Al Shams. The resort is tucked away in the middle of nowhere! About 45 minutes from Dubai and an hour from Abu Dhabi. Upon arrival you are greeted by a small complex created in the style of a desert fort. This has been created with the aim of providing intimate spaces, each equipped with seating areas with cushions for relaxing on.The room was very comfortable with a Arabian theme. All mod cons were sympathically added to maintain the overall illusion. The hotel facilities are excellent and if like us you just want to relax poolside, then this is the place to come. The pool staff are extremely attentive and constantly brought fruit skewers and botles of water to cool us down in the desert sun. At one point I had to turn down the second free ice lolly as I just couldn't manage another one! As we only stayed two nights we were only able to try out two restaurants. The first night we ate at the Al Hadheera. Which whilst having a great selection of food was a little OTT. The theme park style and the entertainment was bearable for one night but on the second we headed to another of the hotels restaurants. The food was again excellent but the quiet, open air, under the stars setting was much more pleasing.Overall we had a fantastic stay and from the moment we arrived till the point of departure the staff could not have been any more helpful.This is one of the few hotels I will consider returning to. If I need a relaxing long weekend away then this has the perfect mix.	
