May 4 2009 	Romantic retreat just outside the city of Dubai	We enjoyed a really lovely 2-night stay at the Bab Al Shams desert resort including a gorgeous aromatherapy massage. Could happily have stayed a few more days, had it not been so ridiculously hot, as there is plenty to do. Hell, there's even an aerobics studio. Surrounded by sand, this hotel - which feels more like a Moroccan Kasbah - has one of the most spectacular swimming pools, or series of swimming pools, I've seen. And a croquet lawn, which does it for me every time. We dined at Al Hadeera: the show is not all that, but the setting is very dramatic and the buffet - especially the mezze and the skewered meats - is pretty good. We also had a pizza and a fatoush at the rooftop restaurant which serves decent cocktails (recommend the Desert something-or-other). Unlike the hotels in the city of Dubai, the soundproofing leaves something to be desired. But at least we knew our neighbours were having an equally, um, romantic stay. Special mention for the wide wrought iron sun loungers around the pool, which really are exceptionally comfortable. A great place for all age groups.	
