Oct 25 2008 	great experience	We stayed at the bab al shams during april 2008. The weather conditions were excellent as extreme heat was not present at this time of the year. The hotel itself has one great advantage. It's in the desert! It is quite a unique feeling. There is no point to review the service only or the size of the bed or the size of the toilet etc, but the whole experience. The design of the hotel is excellent. The theme is that of an Arabian village, with lots of natural materials, narrow 'alleys' and open courtyards with a pool or a water feature, It is really tranquil and isolated therefore it's not a lively holiday destination, Pool facilities are excellent, really nice pools although the water was a bit hot for my standards.. Sun loungers are plentiful and comfortable. Try the extremely cold shower that runs all the time next to the pool system. The rooms are great,clean and plenty of amenities. Book a room that faces the desert and not the inner gardens. It is really nice to wake up and drink your coffee or tea staring at the dunes. The food is nice, as is breakfast. You must try the al hadeerah, Although you feel it is very &quot;touristic&quot; the place is lively ,a very nice setting ,and you get the chance to taste some delicious arabic food or some bbq from the huge selection. It also has live entertainment throughout the evening. If you do the desert safari with a jeep, book to do it early in the morning as the heat makes it uncomfortable later on. However it is not something worth doing. An open top land rover and a driver that drives like a maniac in the middle of the desert.... The final opinion is that the place is worthwhile for a weekend- 3 days max. More than that you get bored.	
