ching these ladies and gents to do their best to satisfy customers. Emmerie especially, tried to keep the place organised and Hanzhi, a waiter, tried very hard to fill the gap of badly needed staff. They both need to be commanded for keeping the otherwise chaotic situation in check. Where was the Management? Very, very unprofessionally handled, topped by very, very, rude reception staff when checking out, for example, when asked whether we had taken something from the minibar and we said no, she called the room service to check immediately! By the way, every time we walked past the reception, someone was complaining. Very strange experience. All in all a Hotel which is not up to standard at all to the rest of Jumeirah Hotels whose Hotels we've been visiting and enjoying in the past at numerous occasions. And no, it was not Ramadan this time!	
