Mar 28 2007 	Service Shambles at Al Shams	On our recent honeymoon we stopped off in dubai and thought it a good idea to sample another side of the Emirates, the desert. The hotel is around an hour by car from Dubai airport and looks great as you approach and enter the grounds. The problem with Al Shams isn't the facilities, grounds or even the food, its the service. The basic premise for what they call service is for the staff to tell someone else, thereby absolving themselves of any responsibility for the room/drink/food/car which you had just ordered.The other major gripe is their lack of pricing on things and although it is a resonably priced resort it is always nice to know what you are being charged. Al Shams certainly isn't a five star resort with an atmosphere akin to an 80's jaunt to spain. The service will annoy people who have stayed in other (good) hotels in the Dubai as Al Shams simply doesn't make the mark.	
