Feb 2 2007	Very Very Nice	After shifting between 3 hotels in 3 nights due to a shortage of over priced accomodation I located this gem in the desert (although the bright lights or Dubai are fast approaching). First thing to remember is Jumeirah is the name of the company which owns the hotel, it is no where near the Jumeriah Beach or Dubai Marina, it's about 70kms away which can take 30 minutes or 2 hours getting out of Dubai at the wrong time of the day! Secondly finding it is a real challenge. I was unable to easily find a map on the web and the tourist map you pick up in Dubai simply points south toward the general location of the resort, most of the roads don't exist. Once here, you'll be in for a treat. Maybe the style is not really local Arabic as they portray in the marketing (more Moroccan than antything as many of the fittings will exhibt) but the ambience is exceptional. I experienced none of the issues with staff that other travellers had mentioned in this website although I was only here as a place to sleep during the working week so I did not use any of the facilities other than the pool, but my laundry was done promptly and the room was immaculate. Never had a bigger (enormous) or more comfortable bed. There were few people around and it was very quiet. The place is a maze to walk around but that adds to the fun of it, you're sure to get lost once trying to find your way back to your room at night. Take your camera, everyone must shoot plenty of pics, the thought put into the design is impressive. It's certainly a destination for honeymoons but there were several families with kids and no one seemed to mind. Make the effort and stay a night or two. I'll be back.	
Jan 5 2007	Beautiful exotic hotel but service standard is irregular	My husband and I stayed at the Bab Al Shams from 24th-27th Dec 2006. The hotel compound is absolutely stunning and it is surrounded by the desert. The rooms are excellent with a bath for two people. We had a room with a view of the desert ; it faces west for stunning sunsets. The best part of the hotel must be the swimming pool. It's beautifully designed with an infinity pool with a background of the sand dunes. The hotel is ideal for a romantic get away rather than for clubbing. It's an hour + away from the city but I loved the space and you could see so many stars in the evening.The dissapointment, however, is the service. It is somtimes good and sometimes aweful, depending on who you are with. One reason, I figured, is because all the staff (save for the guest relations) are from overseas : Indians, Iran,the Philippines etc. My guess is they don't particularly enjoy their lives in Dubai; they are there just for the work. And that reflect in their way of treating people. I try not to take it personally but it does taint the whole experience. In fact, that kind of summarise my experience with Dubai. You hardly meet a local!	
