Nov 25 2006 	Peace and quiet in the desert	We have just returned from a week's trip to Dubai, during which we stayed at Bab Al Shams for 4 nights. We had just stayed at the Ritz-Carlton for 3 nights and absolutely loved it, so were unsure about how we would like Bab Al Shams. Everything isn't perfect at Bab Al Shams, but once we accepted that it wasn't as good and stopped nit-picking, we did enjoy it for what it was.The pools are great, but seriously watched over by about 6 life guards. The water is ozone treated, so not chloriney, and a beautiful temperature. We stayed in for hours.The rooms are really nice - roomy enough, quite stylish, and the bath tub is big enough for 2. There is quite a good choice of restaurants and the roof-top bar is great for drinks after dinner. We weren't that into the music though - a little boring after a while.It does have to be said that the service is not great though. It's like they have read a manual on service, and anything which deviates they just can't accommodate. The quality of the staff is just not up to scratch, although everyone is quite friendly.The spa is very expensive - they had just put the prices up by 20% from the prices that were e-mailed to us. The old prices were pretty much what you would expect in a resort anywhere in the world. The new prices are more than what you would pay in an exclusive spa in London (and their staff costs are miniscule compared to London).The desert drive is also not worth it - one hour driving on dirt roads, a couple of times going up a few sand dunes. It is quite expensive, and we felt it should actually have been offered as a free activity.The highlight of our stay was the horse riding. They use the stables next to the hotel owned by Sheikh Mohammed, and the horses are all Arabian ex-race horses. So with just a little encouragement, they're off. The hard thing was getting them to slow down (usually it's the other way around with trail riding). They do have a ring for beginners though. We enjoyed it so much we went twice. It was such a delight riding through the dunes.Oh, and the pizza is pretty good too. And you can order the pizza from the roof-top bar, if you want to eat in real comfort.All in all, we really enjoyed the stay - just don't go with too high expectations though.	
