May 1 2006	Need a lot more attention to detail to be 5 star	We visited Bal Al Shams for 10 days over Easter. Having taken the overnight flight, we arrived and were told the room wasn't ready- fair enough. We were told 1000 housekeepers were on standby for when guests checked out (quire an achievement since they had 360 staff in total) and to return to the lobby in one hour. We returned - it wasn't ready. We went back an hour later - it wasn't ready. We went back an hour and a half later - it wasn't ready. All this time we had been sitting in the bar in the clothes we travelled in. It was only in response to a direct question at 2.30 that we found out there were shower and changing facilities at the pool. When we eventually went to our room arounf 5pm it was a twin - we had asked for a double. As they were fully booked, we couldn't change until the next day - it took 4 attempts the following day to change rooms, only achieved at 6.30pm - each person on the lobby we spoke to knew nothing about it.Restaurants. The menu was very limited, and the food was average. The service was very slow - there were too many staff, none of whom knew what was going on. The buffet breakfast was good, but on several occasions I had to ask for the chef as he wasn't at his cooking station. As the hotel was fully booked when we arrived, we made a dinner reservation at breakfast on the first morning. When we turned up to dinner, they had no record of the reservation.Rooms. The rooms were ok. The air conditioning temperature couldn't be altered.Pool. The pool was really nice, there were plenty of sunbeds, but they were really noisy when people moved them as they were metal. The pool bar only served drinks, no lunchtime snacks. If you wanted food at lunch, you had to dress and go to the restaurant. Finally, the website and advertising doesn't give the impression that this is a family hotel, so we were disappointed by the number of children at the hotel, and other couples commented on this as well.Not a 5 star hotel, not enough attention to detail, and if I was choosing between this and The Chedi Muscat, I'd go to The Chedi every time. It's a shame, because with better management it could be oitstanding.	
